The optimal thickness of the TPX3 sensor is still debated. A thicker sensor can potentially allow 3D tracking within its volume [75, 76], but at the same time introduces more scattering and leads to creation of more Compton electrons. Our preliminary attempts to do the 3D tracking with 500-μm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
