Which type of the QED U(1) gauge interaction does a quark interact with an antiquark? As pointed out by Yang [159], the quantization and the commensurate properties of the electric charges of the interacting particles imply the compact property of the underlying QED gauge theory. Because (i) quark and antiquark electric charges are quantized and commensurate, (ii) quarks and antiquarks are confined, and (iii) there are experimental evidences for possible occurrence of confined qq¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
